[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rajan steps down from India's central bank

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Raghuram Rajan is one of the more outspoken and colourful of central bankers. But the head of the Reserve Bank of India is leaving his post.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
20 June 2016 Last updated at 01:51 BST
There has been plenty of speculation about his future, and this weekend he announced he will not be signing up for a second term when his contract ends in September.
Sameer Hashmi has more from Mumbai.
